Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the capacity analysis of a communication system, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance of a free-space optical link, which is a type of wireless communication system. 
3. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper presents closed-form expressions for the moments of the end-to-end SNR, which involves optimization and control of the system parameters. 
4. cs.PH (Physics): The paper deals with the physical aspects of a free-space optical link, such as the effect of pointing errors on the system performance. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents an analysis of a communication system that involves both modulation/detection techniques and pointing errors, which can be considered as a control problem.
